	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I just wrote this for my final project for my IB Comp. Sci. class a few months back. I guess I just got around to releasing it. Its not much compared to most other assemblers out but it does support a few things I always wanted in NESASM. 
<br />
<br />Its called <a href="https://github.com/67726e/hasm" class="postlink">hasm</a>. Its probably really buggy right now but it *can* compile. I haven't had the time to write any test games or anything so it may well have some nice bugs.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


